com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface TypeNativePrimitive

All Superinterfaces:
TypeNative
All Known Subinterfaces:
TypeNativeLong
public interface TypeNativePrimitive
extends TypeNative

The TypeNativePrimitive is the interface that represents a native type declaration of a primitive data type (boolean, byte, char, short, int, long, float, double).

Expression syntax if declared the type using a string with NativeTypeManager.dec(String,String[]) or with NativeTypeManager.decPrimitive(Class,String,String) :

PrimitiveTypeName [{MemSizeAndAlignDec}]
Where MemSizeAndAlignDec is defined as:
MemSizeDecList[,AlignSizeDecList]
MemSizeDecList is the memory size of the primitive type and AlignSizeDecList is the preferred alignment, if the alignment is not specified the memory size declared is used as alignment too. The format of both expressions is documented in NativeTypeManager.parseMemorySizeWithMacros(String). Examples:
  • "8"
    The memory size is 8, the alignment is unspecified (will be the same as the declared memory size: 8)
  • "8, 4"
    The memory size is 3 and the preferred alignment 4.
  • "MSC:4;gcc:8;REGISTER_SIZE"
    The memory size is 4 if the "MSC" macro was defined, else is 8 if the "gcc" macro was defined, else the value of the "REGISTER_SIZE" macro is used (must be defined with an integer value). The alignment is unspecified (will be the same as the declared memory size).

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.decPrimitive(Class,long,long), NativeTypeManager.parseMemorySizeWithMacros(String)

Method Detail

decObjectWrapper

TypeNativeObject decObjectWrapper(java.lang.Class clasz)
Declares a native wrapper type of this primitive type.

For instance: if this type is "boolean", the declared data type can be Boolean (the Java wrapper), NativeBoolean and NativeBooleanObject, native instances of these data types are "addressed booleans" and native references are "pointer to boolean".

Parameters:
clasz - the class used to wrap the primitive type.
Returns:
the native wrapper type.
